items.title: Cacomantis flabelliformis, Ptilotula penicillata
items.content_text: This is a mexican standoff. The fan-tailed cuckoo is trying to lay an egg in the white plumed honeyeaters nest. If it succeeds that honeyeater will incubate and raise it as her own.

items.title: Senecio quadridentatus
items.content_text: Typically on the KW Plains I don't see this red form. Both a red and green/grey form were present. Not sure if it is salinity or season or just the way it is.

items.title: Geranium spp.
items.content_text: Not sure about this one. Which geranium is it really? Species 1 looks the closest.

items.title: Eleocharis acuta
items.content_text: Both Eliocharis acuta and E. pallens are present. Distinguishing between the two is difficult (for me). Apparently you need to like at the rhizomes to distinguish these two - that means bending down. E. sphacelata grows to over a metre tall compared to ~3
